-- ZTE Leads Chinese Telecommunications Stocks Higher on Stimulus Speculation
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-22T03:28:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/zte-leads-chinese-telecommunications-stocks-higher-on-stimulus-speculation.html
ZTE Corp. , China’s second-biggest
telephone equipment maker, led telecom companies higher in
Shanghai trading after Citic Securities Co. said the industry
may gain from the government’s five-year plan starting 2011.  ZTE rose 6.2 percent to 28.06 yuan at 11:22 a.m.  China
United Network Communications Ltd.  gained 3 percent to 5.20 yuan.  Indexes tracking telecommunications and technology stocks
on the CSI 300 Index rose 4.4 percent and 5.7 percent,
respectively, the most among 10 industry groups.  -- Irene Shen  in Shanghai. Editor: Richard Frost  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
